      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's just a way to delay the inevitable, isn't it? just staying around out of obligation to \"be seen.\" it feels so exhausting, pretending to be a person when the person is long gone. it's like trying to maintain a museum for something that's already been destroyed. it feels more like a cruelty to keep going when there's nothing left to actually live for.",
